<p class="showcode"><a href="#" >How do I get to the Isle of Wight?</a></p>
<div style="display:none;">
<p>Your route is likely to depend on where you live. The Isle of Wight can be reached by either a car ferry or a passenger ferry from Portsmouth or Lymington via <a href="http://www.wightlink.co.uk" target="_blank">Wightlink Ferries</a> or Southampton via <a href="http://www.redfunnel.co.uk" target="_blank">Red funnel Ferries</a>.<p>
</div>


<p class="showcode"><a href="#" >How far from the ferry port?</a></p>
<div style="display:none;">
<p>Island Retreat is a 5 minute drive away from both Fishbourne car ferry port and Ryde passenger ferry port.</p>
<p>Yarmouth ferry port is about 30 minutes away for those taking the Lymington to Yarmouth ferry route</p>
</div>

